channel.title: Help with 503!
channel.description:
Ok so I downloaded a server. I downloaded the cache. I downloaded the client. But I am having difficulty in getting them to work. I successfully compiled the client, but whenever I try and run it it comes up with: [code]Usage: worldid, <live/office/local>, <live/rc/wip>, <software/hardware>, <free/members>, <english/german>, <game0/game1> [safemode][/code] Then it closes.
What do I need to do to get it working?
Please help all answers appreciated.
P Aii N in the ass.[br][br][size=1]Posted on: August 11, 2008, 08:13:59 am[/size][hr]Anyone?
LiL Help?[br][br][size=1]Posted on: August 11, 2008, 08:18:13 am[/size][hr]Ok so I fixed that problem.
But Now!!!
THe client opens and says connecting to Update Server Please Wait. And it NEVER loads.
Also in the CMD
It says "error_game_js5connect"
what is that and how do I get it working?

item.title: Help with 503!
item.dc:creator: @WrittenBlade WrittenBlade
item.description:
@WrittenBlade wrote:

The error_game_js5connect means the server the client is connected to is offline. You need to run the server first before running the client.
